citations:
    citation-acok-tyrion-xiv:
        source: source-acok
        properties:
            locator: "Tyrion XIV"
            text_from_source: "Motionless as a gargoyle, Tyrion Lannister hunched on one knee atop a merlon. Beyond the Mud Gate and the desolation that had once been the fishmarket and wharves, the river itself seemed to have taken fire. Half of Stannis's fleet was ablaze, along with most of Joffrey's. The kiss of wildfire turned proud ships into funeral pyres and men into living torches."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Tyrion's POV at the Mud Gate watching the wildfire destroy the fleets. He commands sorties, witnesses the Hound's refusal and desertion, then leads the sortie himself from the King's Gate with Ser Mandon Moore and Podrick Payne at his side. He is attacked by Mandon Moore on the bridge of boats — face slashed — and saved by Podrick Payne who pushes Moore into the river. Note: citation-acok-tyrion-xv in this archive covers a related Tyrion chapter (wildfire/fleet destruction) — these are the two consecutive Tyrion battle chapters."
